d nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=garbhad>Garbhad</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Brainbender</span><br>  Posts: 423<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/12/00 9:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My Take on Shadow Knights</span><hr size=1> OK i have a new shadow knight as my secondary. He is level 12 now and was soloing derv's in nro at level 9. People wrere telling met hat there is no way i should be able to do so. However, i was able to do it with ease. There is so much unbridled power in an sk that people just do not realize it. <br>
<br>
My SK is a Erudite, he has a high int as well as str. This gives him a large mana pool with an exceptional ability to do some serious damage. The spell line leaves alittle to be desired but you can very easily make real good use of the spells you are given.<br>
<br>
I would say in a fight with a red con at that level i would lose a bubble of health per fight. Now i know at higher levels i won't be able to do it but by basis of comparison, SK's are really true damage dealers. Third only to Rogues and monks respectively. <br>
<br>
Now given my SK is equipped with a MoSS, Arbitor's combine great sword, Fungi tunic blood ember and darkforge mix as well as mithril and the best jewelry money can buy. He can deal some sweet damage. Now i went back to using a M2H and Dark Reaver. I was still able to whip out 20-35 point shots per hit. At level 12 that is quite a bit of damage, add life tap and steal strength on top of it and that makes for a nasty combo. <br>
<br>
Some say I should have made a Troll or Ogre SK, WHY ?<br>
Why waste the ability to tap a precious resource like mana, by not making him a erudite. I find i have more mana than my hunting partner who happens to be a level 12 Ogre SK. Granted the int limit on Ogre and trolls pales in comparison, but that is where my point lies. An Sk is a fighting necro. Put those spells to use and don't be afraid to be the main tank. If someone says &quot;oh you are a hybrid, we wanted a real tank.&quot; Then they have never seen a real tank because an SK can soak up as much damage if not more than a warrior.<br>
<br>
Next Update at level 20<br>
