Andy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ulothe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lothe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(12/1/00 5:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> SK's</span><hr size=1> As a career SK, and one of the few people over level 50 with no twinks or alts, I consider myself a guru on the class. You ask why choose a large race? Well I can explain why I chose ogre, and not troll, and why I'd recommend nothing BUT ogre for an SK.<br>
<br>
First, as it has been mentioned, the no-stun-from-the-front ability of an ogre is something no one can truly appreciate until they've had the ability long enough to take it for granted. I have quite a hard time adapting to other characters when I play them for this reason. When I am being pummeled, unless I get knocked back considerably, I can channel through nearly anything. Bash's from mobs are nothing more than an extra attack, and have no further ability to interrupt than a normal attack when you are an ogre.<br>
<br>
Second, hit points and STR. I see plenty of people saying how the difference is negligible. I say, you're full of crap if you think that. BUTT ASS NAKED, I have a few hundred more hp than other SK's. The fact that I must invest less in maintaining str has allowed me the option of several high-hp items. This in addition to my natural 130 STA goes a long way. Fact: Ogres have more starting stat points than ANY OTHER race in the game.<br>
<br>
Third, bash w/2hand. nuff said.<br>
<br>
Fourth, and something that I've rarely seen mentioned anywhere, is the fact that loss of stamina (the yellow bar) has no adverse affect on Ogres aside from not being able to jump. When an Ogre's stamina depletes, his combat does not slow, nor do his physical stats deteriorate like other races. You simply can't jump. That's it.<br>
<br>
Fifth, lower exp table than Troll or Iksar. Simply put, trolls offer nowhere near the advantages of Ogres. You pay a full 5% more exp for regen that really won't matter in the long run despite what Troll lovers will insist. SK's depend on taps to heal while soloing, and you get heals in a group. BFD, a troll ticks back a whole 2 or 3 more points, but has noticably worse stats to boot, and does not share the ogres physical advatages listed above.<br>
<br>
In regards to the mana issue, yes this is quite a concern. However I attest it is irrelevant if your SK is a twink. The reasoning is simple: Ogres have outrageos physical stats. With this in mind, invest nothing in INT, but rely on your gear to boost it. Currently my SK has over 100 INT, and with the completion of the epic, plus several other items in my near future, this number will rocket to 130-140; More than enough mana for ANY hybrid. Combine this with the fact that many high end hybrid items contain +mana, and you'll find this becomes a non-issue. Using the hill giant comparison as a point of reference, I can solo them with 1 cast dooming, and 1 or 2 casts of Invoke Fear; a paltry bubble-and-a-half of mana. The bare truth about an SK is that you are first and foremost a warrior. Your spells present little to no aid for a group, therefore you shortchange your SK's ability by investing heavily in INT/choosing an INT heavy race.<br>
<br>
And finally: Infravision. At higher levels SK's have spells for both infra and ultravisions, but you won't be thinking that when you're level 20 and can't see the giant who is hammering you into the sand.<br>
<br>
I'm done. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/uandvarishadowmist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AndvariShadowmist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bastard Bard</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(12/5/00 11:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SK's</span><hr size=1> Hum for the stamina running down yet not slowing down part.. that is the way it is for everyone with 100+ Stamina me thinks.<br>
