p align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SK's</span><hr size=1> <br>
 Lothe:<br>
<br>
 The stamina thing isn't ogre specific. Any char with &gt; 100 base stamia is unaffected when the yellow bar goes to empty. Otherwisse you start losing other stats when stamina gets too low.<br>
<br>
  As for whoever it was that loves their DE sk. Great, more power to you, play a class you love. I love my HE magician, but he's basically useless for anything except COTH on raids now (thanks verant for 100% MR 200k hp mobs). From a pure powergaming standpoint, however, an ogre SK is just plain a better SK for all the reasons lothe has just outlined.<br>
<br>
   The question isn't whether a DE sk is viable (it obviously is, I know of several &gt; 50 in my guild), or fun to play (again, it obviously is, you'd have to be sick to level a sk up above 50 unless you really liked it), but rather whether it is the optimal race/class combination.<br>
<br>
   For better or worse, there are optimal race/class combo's from a powergaming standpoint.<br>
<br>
   Ogres make the best warriors or SK.<br>
   Barbarians make the best shamans.<br>
   Barbarians make the best rogues.<br>
   Iksars make the best monks.<br>
<br>
   I personally would never play an ogre. My warrior twink (lvl 4<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , is a barbarian because the large race thing bugs me. I hate being in the way all the time. Likewise, I'd never start a barbarian rogue as a non twink. The night blindness thing drives me ape shit.<br>
<br>
   So it really depends what you want. The problem with threads like this is people always ask &quot;what race makes the *best* &lt;insert class here&gt;&quot; What they really should ask is &quot;what race/class combo will I *enjoy* the most&quot;.<br>
<br>
   An ogre is a better sk than a DE. If I had to play a sk though, I'd prolly go DE, because I don't *enjoy* being a fatty.<br>
